Definition: restrict or confine within limits
Example: I limit you to two visits to the pub a day; please confine your questions to the topic; our actions are circumscribed by our biology, personality, and by the social and cultural context into which we are born
Synonyms: noun, attribute, time, limitation, cognition, act, circumscribe, circumscription, confine_to, decrease, restrict, or, confine, within, limits, I, you, to, two, visits, the, pub, a, day, please, your, questions, topic, our, actions, are, circumscribed, by, biology, personality, and, social, cultural, context, into, which, we, born
Frame: 8,11
Category: verb.change
